<http://knuckles.team/kg/worldview> a owl:Ontology ;
    rdfs:label "WorldView Subject-Domain Ontology" ;
    rdfs:comment """The canonical upper taxonomy of world-knowledge subject domains every
:Topic classification hangs from. A curated, reasonably-MECE top level (Science,
Technology & Computing, Engineering, Mathematics, Health & Medicine, Society &
Politics, Economy & Business, Law & Governance, Environment & Earth, Arts &
Culture, Humanities & Philosophy, Sports & Recreation), each with a first layer
of sub-domains, expressed as a SKOS concept scheme. Documents are classified onto
the most specific node they justify; deeper, context-derived sub-topics attach as
skos:narrower beneath the nearest node here, so the whole ingested corpus
organizes under one worldview instead of floating per-document tags.""" ;
    owl:imports <http://knuckles.team/kg> .

:topic-mathematics a :Topic,
        :WorldViewDomain ;
    rdfs:label "Mathematics" ;
    skos:inScheme :WorldViewScheme ;
    skos:prefLabel "Mathematics" ;
    skos:topConceptOf :WorldViewScheme .

:topic-sports-recreation a :Topic,
        :WorldViewDomain ;
    rdfs:label "Sports & Recreation" ;
    skos:inScheme :WorldViewScheme ;
